post_text:
FALL SPORTS REGISTRATION

Ely High School will hold fall sports registration meetings on Wednesday, August 12, and Thursday, August 13, outdoors at the baseball field (Veterans Memorial Field) to allow for social distancing.

Meetings will be held as follows:

‚Ä¢ Boys Cross Country - Wednesday, Aug. 12, 6 pm;
‚Ä¢ Girls Cross Country - Wednesday, Aug. 12, 7 pm.

‚Ä¢ Girls Swimming and Soccer - Thursday, Aug. 13, 6 pm.

Meetings are for participants in grades 7-12 and their parents. Coaches for cross country and girls swimming will be present for meetings, while soccer sign-up will be held to gauge interest in the new cooperative with Mesabi East, which hosts and conducts the girls soccer program.

The remaining fall activities have been moved to new seasons, with football and volleyball to be conducted during the spring and dance team delayed until the start of the winter season.

For more information, contact athletic director Tom Coombe at Tcoombe@ely.12.mn.us, or at (218) 235-1025.

post_text:
Congratulations to our senior class of 2020 on your incredible accomplishment. It is because of you all that our school is the place it is today. Thank you for your leadership of your fellow students and your hard work that brought you to this point. We look forward to all you will accomplish in the future.
Your high school career ended in an unconventional manner, one that no one could have predicted. In the same way, I'm sure the class of 2020 will surprise us with the places they will go and all they will accomplish.

"I wish it need not have happened in my time," said Frodo.
"So do I," said Gandalf, "and so do all who live to see such times. But that is not for them to decide. All we have to decide is what to do with the time that is given us."
--J.R.R. Tolkien

Embark with our balloon on a journey of nearly out-of-this-world proportions and get a view of what only astronauts see on their way to space.

post_text:
Ely Public Schools Update on COVID -19
March 20, 2020
Dear Families,
We have been in daily contact with the Minnesota Department of Education and are continuing
to monitor the status of COVID-19 as it relates to schools.
During the March 18th - March 27th School Closure Period, mandated by Governor Walz, the
Ely Public School District will continue to plan for distance learning in the event the closure goes beyond March 27th. However, during this period teachers may be contacting families to determine their needs for Distance Learning.
While educational services will not be provided during the Closure Period of March 18 - March
27, the District is providing meals and childcare as mandated by Governor Walz.
As always, our first priority is the safety and well-being of our students. We also want to ensure
every child has access to the education they need and deserve.
We will continue to keep you informed as we navigate COVID-19.

Sincerely,
Superintendent Erie
Principal Anderson
Principal Oelke
Facilities/Transportation Director Leeson

Memorial Middle School is raising money for its activities: Wolf Ridge Trip, Giants Ridge, Lego Robotics etc. Direct-from-the-grower oranges and grapefruit are being sold by the 20 pound case, $30/case. post_text: This week the Quiltmaker's Gift will be performed at the Ely Theater and students enjoyed a close-up look at the illustrator's watercolor paintings last week. Gail de Marcken visited with all 3 high school art classes last Friday. She shared some of the spreads that she painted for her books. Students enjoyed listening to her share her adventures from around the world, what it's like to be an illustrator, and how much time and care she puts into each piece.
